(firstQuint)Safety Evaluation of Bowel Cleansing Regimen for PillCam COLON 2 Capsule Endoscopy.

 The preparation regimen used for the PillCam(R) Colon 2 procedure consists of several colon cleansing materials.

 Different combinations of the above regimen were tested and evaluated for safety by monitoring of adverse events in multiple clinical studies, with more than 1000 subjects enrolled to date.

 No Serious Adverse Events related to the preparation were noted.

 In this study, each subject will be required to undergo serum chemistry tests (blood tests) at several time points to evaluate the safety of the regimen.

 No capsule ingestion is involved.

